	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: 2013: One Gameboy project per week</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I can think of two reasons.<br />1) The guy who was good CPLD programming quit and they could no longer get the old logic to work.<br />2) They wanted to use a cheaper CPLD to save money. However, looking at the datasheet, both the old and new CPLD have 64 macrocells, so superficially it shouldn't matter unless the new chip was incompatible with the old layout. <br />Or, there IS master protection in hardware which no one knows how to access, and is not used by any known menu ROM. Maybe I should ask EMS about this, but previously when I've asked about technical details about their products, they have just said it was a secret they couldn't share.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


